+{"id":"asupersync-8w83i.32","title":"[FABRIC][consumer] Tail pull resolution must not replay acked tail messages","description":"Bounded child under asupersync-8w83i. In src/messaging/consumer.rs, resolve_pull_window() resolves ConsumerDemandClass::Tail from available_tail alone. When a consumer is fully caught up (available_tail <= ack_floor), or when fewer than batch_size messages remain unacked near the tail, the current logic can re-serve already acknowledged sequences instead of waiting for new data or shrinking the window to the unacked suffix. Tighten tail pull resolution to respect ack_floor fail-closed, add focused regressions for fully caught-up and partially-caught-up tail requests, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo gates.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentChapel","owner":"SilentChapel","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-04-01T17:17:51.310858144Z","created_by":"SilentChapel","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:18:02.354667415Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["consumer","fabric","messaging","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.32","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:17:51.310858144Z","created_by":"SilentChapel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2848,"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.32","author":"SilentChapel","text":"2026-04-01 SilentChapel: fixing src/messaging/consumer.rs so ConsumerDemandClass::Tail respects ack_floor. Root bug: tail resolution previously used available_tail alone, which could replay already acknowledged messages when the consumer was fully caught up or near-tail caught up. Patch landed with focused regressions for waiting-when-caught-up and clamping-to-unacked-suffix; moving into rch-backed validation now.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:18:02Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-8w83i.4","title":"[FABRIC][P3] Import/Export Morphisms & Transform Algebra","description":"# Phase 3: Import/Export Morphisms & Transform Algebra\n\n## Purpose\nModel cross-domain namespace edges as typed namespace morphisms instead of plain routing rules. Each morphism carries independently checkable facets for authority, reversibility, secrecy, cost, and observability.\n\n## Morphism Classification\nEvery morphism is classified as one of:\n- **authoritative**: reversible, reply-authoritative, capability-bearing\n- **derived-view**: may redact/summarize/reorder within declared law, but cannot originate authority\n- **egress**: one-way export into weaker trust or replay domains\n- **delegation**: temporary sub-language handoff with bounded time, budget, and revocation semantics\n\n## Morphism Specification\nEach morphism defines:\n- Source and destination subject language\n- Allowed transform algebra (wildcard capture, deterministic hash-based partitioning, split/slice, left/right extraction)\n- Reversibility requirements\n- Capability requirements\n- Sharing policy for metadata and identity\n- Privacy and metadata disclosure policy\n- Optional attestation or private-compliance proof policy\n- Response policy\n- Quota and budget policy\n\n## Five Independently Checkable Facets\n1. Authority\n2. Reversibility\n3. Secrecy and metadata exposure\n4. Cost and quota envelope\n5. Observability and evidence obligations\n\n## Transform Algebra Design\n- Must stay finite, decidable, and explainable (not an embedded scripting problem)\n- Deterministic core for authority-bearing edges\n- Randomized or irreversible transforms ONLY on one-way non-authoritative fanout paths\n- Reversible transforms required for authority-bearing edges\n- NATS-inspired: wildcard capture, hash-based partitioning, split/slice, left/right extraction, strict mode\n\n## Key Features\n- Definition-time validation of reversibility where required\n- Cycle detection with semantic classes (not just string collision)\n- Explicit policy + enforcement that cross-domain requests produce replies only in permitted reply spaces\n- Auditable reasoning about what metadata crosses a boundary\n- Compiled morphism certificates as inspectable artifacts\n\n## Relation to Existing Code\n- distributed/bridge.rs has cross-node bridge concepts with sequence advance\n- distributed/encoding.rs has encoding/distribution logic\n- transport/router.rs has RoutingTable with EndpointId routing\n\n## FABRIC North Star Reference\nThis phase is governed by the five cross-cutting FABRIC success criteria defined in `src/messaging/mod.rs` and `docs/FABRIC_GUARDRAILS.md`:\n1. Keep the public mental model NATS-small.\n2. Make stronger guarantees explicit named service classes, never hidden taxes on the common case.\n3. Lower radical behavior into small, inspectable artifacts.\n4. Keep autonomous policy loops inside declared safety envelopes with replay, evidence, and rollback.\n5. Target the first product wedge at systems that need sovereignty, durable partial progress, and post-incident explanation together.\n\nIf work in this phase violates those criteria, or drifts toward the anti-goal of a grand unified fabric that makes the common case slower and less legible than NATS, it must be redesigned.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:08.777353354Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:52:28.546229805Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T06:52:28.546203706Z","close_reason":"All 4 subtasks closed: morphism type system, transform algebra, cycle detection, unit tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fabric","federation","morphism","transform"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:08.777353354Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:05:02.464794729Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.1","title":"[FABRIC][P3.1] Define morphism type system","description":"Define the typed namespace morphism system. File: src/messaging/morphism.rs\n\n- MorphismClass enum: Authoritative (reversible, reply-authoritative, capability-bearing), DerivedView (redact/summarize/reorder within declared law, no authority origination), Egress (one-way export into weaker trust/replay domains), Delegation (temporary sub-language handoff with bounded time/budget/revocation)\n- Morphism struct with: source_language (SubjectPattern), dest_language (SubjectPattern), class (MorphismClass), transform (SubjectTransform), reversibility (ReversibilityRequirement), capability_requirements (Vec<FabricCapability>), sharing_policy (SharingPolicy), privacy_policy (PrivacyPolicy), response_policy (ResponsePolicy), quota_policy (QuotaPolicy)\n- Five independently checkable facets: authority, reversibility, secrecy/metadata exposure, cost/quota envelope, observability/evidence obligations\n- MorphismCertificate: compiled and verified morphism artifact\n- Tests: morphism construction, class validation, facet independence","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"PinkSparrow","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:21:32.359246780Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T01:41:45.316166550Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T01:41:45.137341599Z","close_reason":"Implemented typed morphism system and validated with check+tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fabric","morphism","types"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:21:32.359246780Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2526,"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"NATS implementation reference: server/accounts.go shows the import/export graph with stream exports, service exports, imports, response tracking, service latency reporting, and cycle detection. server/subject_transform.go shows the transform vocabulary. Key difference from NATS: our morphisms carry five independently checkable facets (authority, reversibility, secrecy, cost, observability) and are classified into four classes (authoritative, derived-view, egress, delegation). NATS has no concept of reversibility requirements or privacy disclosure policy on cross-boundary edges. The transform algebra must stay finite and decidable — NATS achieved this by constraining transforms to specific operations (wildcard capture, hash partition, split/slice, left/right extract). We keep that constraint but add a strict reversibility check for authority-bearing edges.","created_at":"2026-03-17T16:48:57Z"},{"id":2553,"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.1","author":"PinkSparrow","text":"Implemented typed FABRIC morphism surface in src/messaging/morphism.rs with class taxonomy, capability/reversibility/sharing/response/quota policy types, facet extraction, deterministic MorphismCertificate compilation, and unit coverage for class validation, facet independence, and duplicate capability rejection. Validation: rch exec cargo check --all-targets --features messaging-fabric exited 0; rch exec cargo test -p asupersync --features messaging-fabric morphism --lib passed (19 tests). Known repo-wide drift remains outside this bead: cargo fmt --check reports formatting differences in unrelated files, and cargo clippy --all-targets --features messaging-fabric -D warnings still fails on unrelated pre-existing lints in lab/stream/messaging subject+ir files. MCP Agent Mail endpoint was unavailable during wrap-up, so I could not post the normal completion thread or release reservations there.","created_at":"2026-03-19T01:40:45Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.2","title":"[FABRIC][P3.2] Build transform algebra","description":"Implement the subject transform algebra inspired by NATS server/subject_transform.go. File: src/messaging/morphism.rs (transform portion)\n\n- SubjectTransform enum with operations: WildcardCapture (capture tokens from pattern match), DeterministicHash (hash-based partitioning — deterministic, no randomness), SplitSlice (split token and take slice), LeftExtract / RightExtract (prefix/suffix extraction), Identity (no-op), Compose (chain transforms)\n- Transform must stay finite, decidable, and explainable\n- Deterministic core for authority-bearing edges\n- Randomized/irreversible transforms ONLY on one-way non-authoritative fanout paths (enforced by type system)\n- ReversibilityRequirement: Required (compile-time check that transform is invertible), Preferred (warn if not invertible), NotRequired\n- Reversibility checker: given a transform, can we compute the inverse?\n- Tests: all transform operations, composition, reversibility checking, determinism verification","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"BlackMeadow","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:21:42.503028640Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-20T19:59:15.072538228Z","closed_at":"2026-03-20T19:59:15.072514404Z","close_reason":"Completed: delegation morphisms now reject lossy or irreversible transforms; focused morphism tests green; check green; clippy blocked elsewhere","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fabric","morphism","transform"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:21:42.503028640Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-8w83i.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-17T07:22:05.632401495Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
